FA1: Please check your internet connection. Are you able to download other apps? If not, we suggest you clear the cache and data of the Google Play Store and try again.
FA10: If your QR code is not working, request your manager at your organization to provide you with a new one. QR codes for associate apps are customer-specific and cannot be provided directly from Reflexis support.
FA11: First, ask your manager to provide a new QR code. Work with your manager to see if the new QR code is working on any other associate/store devices aside from your personal device. If the code is not working on any devices, raise a support ticket through your own organization’s Help Desk.
FA12: Check with your manager to ensure your account has been activated in the system. If you have verified that your account is active, try accessing the same Reflexis application through a desktop (web) interface. If the login credentials do not work on the desktop application, report to your organization’s support that your login is not working.
FA13: App issues can be reported by navigating to the Setting menu and tapping 'Report an Issue'. When using the Report an Issue function, kindly provide your organization details alongside your issue.
FA14: If you are not scheduled for any day, the app will show you as not scheduled. If you believe this is in error, contact your manager for scheduling details. If you see errors with the schedule page interface, navigate to the Settings menu and tap 'Report an Issue' to communicate the issue to Reflexis. When using the Report an Issue function, kindly provide your organization details alongside your issue.
FA2: Location services are required if your organization has set up the functionality to allow app users to log in/clock in while being nearby to their store. Please discuss this with your organization if you do not wish to use your location services.
FA3: Please ask your Manager at your organization to provide a new QRCode. QRCode is customer-specific so we can’t provide any QRCodes specific to your organization.
FA4: Please ask your Manager at your organization to provide a new QRCode and check with your manager if the new QRCode is working in any other associate or store devices. If unable to scan still, please raise a support ticket through your organization's help desk.
FA5: Please check with your manager if your account has been activated inside the system. Perform additional validation to see if you can access the Reflexis application using desktop(web) login provided. Report to your organization if your login doesn’t work
FA6: Report an issue from Settings > Report an Issue. Also, provide us your organization details while reporting the issue.
FA7: Hello, if you are not scheduled for any day, it will be shown as not schedule.d Please contact your manager for that. If you see any error on the schedule page, please report an issue.
FA8: First, confirm that your internet connection is functioning properly. If it is, check that you are able to download and install other apps successfully. If you are unable to download any apps at all, please try to clear the cache and data of the Play/App store and try again.
FA9: If your organization has set up the functionality within the app to allow users to log in/clock-in while being near their store. Location services are required to be enabled. Consult your organization if you do not wish to enable Location Services for this app.
